{
  "stem": "11964.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "For example, without exception, whether persons-- Jewish people, may have been very religious or not religious at all, on Friday night at sunset, all Jewish establishments would close.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "All the stores would absolutely close and reopen Saturday night after sundown.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "No matter what kind of business they would have anticipated, this was something that was adhered to.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that, of course, took place also during the holidays.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Not only would the stores be closed, but all the artisans would stop working.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "A tailor or a-- or a-- any-- any other artisan would stop working, because on a Shabbat a Jew does not work.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He doesn't necessarily have to go to the house of prayer, but he just doesn't work.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My father went to the house of prayer.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "My father was an ardent Zionist.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But he was also a Mizrachi Zionist, which means he was a religious Zionist.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he would-- on a Friday night after he would close his store, he would change his clothes, and he would go into a little synagogue, which is called-- was called shtiebel.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And there are very many shtiebels that different people frequented.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "My father would go to the shtiebel on a Friday night.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And my mother and the children would go upstairs, got themselves ready for the Shabbat, and the table would be set.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we would wait for our father to come home, and then we would have the Shabbat meal.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the Shabbat meal was always a very traditional meal.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, on a Friday, my mother, who would help my father usually in the store-- on a Friday morning she would go upstairs.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
